Can you enlighten us? What's Barcamp?

Barcamp is an unconference where the attendees make the conference. So each day attendees can place a talk on the 'grid'..which is a 25 minute talk, we can have 5 in parallel in the venue we use and they can talk about anything they want in those 25mins
So this year we had all sorts from how to make cheese, balloon animals, fighting robots, how TV works, how to make retro's better

It's really awesome. It's not a strictly Manchester event but we do hold one in Manchester annually. It took a break in 2017 as previous organiser didn't have time but 4 of us have taken over and brought it back this year
And I was meant to go, but was hungover on both days, which reflects terribly on me :D
